project.name: Settlers Domain v1
project.description:
This one was for the numeric track of the IPC-3 and proved to be a very tough resource management domain. Several interesting issues in encoding arise as well as the subsequent problem of planning with the domain. In particular, resources can be combined to construct vehicles of various kinds. Since these vehicles are not available initially, this is an example of a problem in which new objects are created. PDDL does not conveniently support this concept at present, so it is necessary to name "potential" vehicles at the outset, which can be realised through construction. A very high degree of redundant symmetry exists between these "potential" vehicles, since it does not matter which vehicle names are actually used for the vehicles that are realised in a plan. Planners that begin by grounding all actions can be swamped by the large numbers of potential actions involving these potential vehicles, which could be realised as one of several different types of actual vehicles.
Plan quality is judged by a linear combination of labour use, pollution creation and resource consumption. There is scope for constructing very hard metrics that involve maximising housing construction subject to an increasing pollution penalty (say), to ensure that optimal plan quality is bounded.
The domain was introduced by Maria Fox and Derek Long in IPC-3. It was also used in IPC-4. This model is based on the IPC-4 pddl model.

operator.name: buildCabin
operator.constraints:
pre: p.woodland = true
post: labour = labour + 1 and p.hasCabin = true

operator.name: buildQuarry
operator.constraints:
pre: p.mountain = true
post: labour = labour + 2 and p.hasQuarry = true

operator.name: buildCoalStack
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(timber) >= 1
post: labour = labour + 2 and p.available(timber) = p.available(timber) - 1 and p.hasCoalStack = true

operator.name: buildSawmill
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(timber) >= 2
post: labour = labour + 2 and p.available(timber) = p.available(timber) - 2 and p.hasSawmill = true

operator.name: buildMine
operator.constraints:
pre: p.metalliferous = true and p.available(wood) >= 2
post: labour = labour + 3 and p.available(wood) = p.available(wood) - 2 and p.hasMine = true

operator.name: buildIronworks
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(stone) >= 2 and p.available(wood) >= 2
post: labour = labour + 3 and p.available(stone) = p.available(stone) - 2 and p.available(wood) = p.available(wood) - 2 and p.hasIronworks = true

operator.name: buildDocks
operator.constraints:
pre: p.byCoast = true and p.available(stone) >= 2 and p.available(wood) >= 2
post: labour = labour + 2 and p.available(stone) = p.available(stone) - 2 and p.available(wood) = p.available(wood) - 2 and p.hasDocks = true

operator.name: buildWharf
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasDocks = true and p.available(stone) >= 2 and p.available(iron) >= 2
post: labour = labour + 2 and p.available(stone) = p.available(stone) - 2 and p.available(iron) = p.available(iron) - 2 and p.hasWharf = true

operator.name: buildRail
operator.constraints:
pre: p1.connectedByLand->exists(x:Place|x = p2) and p1.available(wood) >= 1 and p1.available(iron) >= 1
post: labour = labour + 2 and p1.available(wood) = p1.available(stone) - 1 and p1.available(iron) = p1.available(iron) - 1 and p1.connectedByRail->includes(p2)

operator.name: buildHouse
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(stone) >= 1 and p.available(wood) >= 1
post: p.housing = p.housing + 1 and p.available(stone) = p.available(stone) - 1 and p.available(wood) = p.available(wood) - 1

operator.name: buildCart
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(timber) >= 1 and v.potential = true
post: p.available(timber) = p.available(timber) - 1 and v.potential = false and v.isAt = p and v.isCart = true and v.spaceIn = 1 and v.available(timber) = 0 and v.available(wood) = 0 and v.available(coal) = 0 and v.available(stone) = 0 and v.available(iron) = 0 and v.available(ore) = 0 and labour = labour + 1

operator.name: buildTrain
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(iron) >= 2 and v.potential = true
post: p.available(iron) = p.available(iron) - 2 and v.potential = false and v.isAt = p and v.isTrain = true and v.spaceIn = 5 and v.available(timber) = 0 and v.available(wood) = 0 and v.available(coal) = 0 and v.available(stone) = 0 and v.available(iron) = 0 and v.available(ore) = 0 and labour = labour + 2

operator.name: buildShip
operator.constraints:
pre: p.available(iron) >= 4 and v.potential = true
post: p.hasWharf = true and p.available(iron) = p.available(iron) - 4 and v.potential = false and v.isAt = p and v.isShip = true and v.spaceIn = 10 and v.available(timber) = 0 and v.available(wood) = 0 and v.available(coal) = 0 and v.available(stone) = 0 and v.available(iron) = 0 and v.available(ore) = 0 and labour = labour + 3

operator.name: fellTimber
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasCabin = true
post: p.available(timber) = p.available(timber) + 1 and labour = labour + 1

operator.name: breakStone
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasQuarry = true
post: p.available(stone) = p.available(stone) + 1 and labour = labour + 1 and resourceUse = resourceUse + 1

operator.name: mineOre
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasMine = true
post: p.available(ore) = p.available(ore) + 1 and resourceUse = resourceUse + 1

operator.name: burnCoal
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasCoalStack = true and p.available(timber) >= 1
post: p.available(timber) = p.available(timber) - 1 and p.available(coal) = p.available(coal) + 1 and pollution = pollution + 1

operator.name: sawWood
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasSawmill = true and p.available(timber) >= 1
post: p.available(timber) = p.available(timber) - 1 and p.available(wood) = p.available(wood) + 1

operator.name: makeIron
operator.constraints:
pre: p.hasIronworks = true and p.available(ore) >= 1 and p.available(coal) >= 2
post: p.available(ore) = p.available(ore) - 1 and p.available(coal) = p.available(coal) - 2 and p.available(iron) = p.available(iron) + 1 and pollution = pollution + 2

action.precondition: v.isAt = p and p.available(r) > 0 and v.spaceIn > 0
action.postcondition: v.spaceIn = v.spaceIn - 1 and v.available(r) = v.available(r) + 1 and p.available(r) = p.available(r) - 1 and labour = labour + 1
v.spaceIn = v.spaceIn + 1 and v.available(r) = v.available(r) - 1 and p.available(r) = p.available(r) + 1 and labour = labour + 1

action.precondition: v.isCart = true and p1.connectedByLand->exists(x:Place|x = p2) and v.isAt = p1
v.isTrain = true and p1.connectedByRail->exists(x:Place|x = p2) and v.isAt = p1 and v.available(coal) >= 1
action.postcondition: v.isAt = p2 and v.available(coal) = v.available(coal) - 1 and pollution = pollution + 1

action.precondition: v.isTrain = true and p1.connectedBySea->exists(x:Place|x = p2) and v.isAt = p1 and v.available(coal) >= 2
action.postcondition: v.isAt = p2 and v.available(coal) = v.available(coal) - 2 and pollution = pollution + 2
